  22:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c ****   @verbatim
  23:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c ****   ==============================================================================
  24:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c ****                     ##### GPIO Peripheral features #####
  25:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c ****   ==============================================================================
  26:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c ****   [..]
  27:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c ****     (+) Each port bit of the general-purpose I/O (GPIO) ports can be individually
  28:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c ****         configured by software in several modes:
  29:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c ****         (++) Input mode
  30:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c ****         (++) Analog mode
  31:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c ****         (++) Output mode
  32:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c ****         (++) Alternate function mode
  33:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c ****         (++) External interrupt/event lines
  34:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c **** 
  35:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c ****     (+) During and just after reset, the alternate functions and external interrupt
  36:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c ****         lines are not active and the I/O ports are configured in analog mode.
  37:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c **** 
  38:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c ****     (+) All GPIO pins have weak internal pull-up and pull-down resistors, which can be
  39:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c ****         activated or not.
  40:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c **** 
  41:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c ****     (+) In Output or Alternate mode, each IO can be configured on open-drain or push-pull
  42:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c ****         type and the IO speed can be selected depending on the VDD value.
  43:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c **** 
  44:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c ****     (+) The microcontroller IO pins are connected to onboard peripherals/modules through a
  45:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c ****         multiplexer that allows only one peripheral alternate function (AF) connected
  46:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c ****         to an IO pin at a time. In this way, there can be no conflict between peripherals
  47:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c ****         sharing the same IO pin.
  48:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c **** 
  49:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c ****     (+) All ports have external interrupt/event capability. To use external interrupt
  50:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c ****         lines, the port must be configured in input mode. All available GPIO pins are
  51:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c ****         connected to the 16 external interrupt/event lines from EXTI0 to EXTI15.
  52:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c **** 
  53:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c ****     (+) The external interrupt/event controller consists of up to 73 edge detectors
  54:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c ****         (16 lines are connected to GPIO) for generating event/interrupt requests (each
  55:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c ****         input line can be independently configured to select the type (interrupt or event)
  56:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c ****         and the corresponding trigger event (rising or falling or both). Each line can
  57:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c ****         also be masked independently.
  58:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c **** 
  59:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c ****                      ##### How to use this driver #####
  60:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c ****   ==============================================================================
  61:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c ****   [..]
  62:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c ****     (#) Enable the GPIO AHB clock using the following function: __HAL_RCC_GPIOx_CLK_ENABLE().
  63:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c **** 
  64:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c ****     (#) Configure the GPIO pin(s) using HAL_GPIO_Init().
  65:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c ****         (++) Configure the IO mode using "Mode" member from GPIO_InitTypeDef structure
  66:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c ****         (++) Activate Pull-up, Pull-down resistor using "Pull" member from GPIO_InitTypeDef
  67:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c ****              structure.
  68:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c ****         (++) In case of Output or alternate function mode selection: the speed is
  69:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c ****              configured through "Speed" member from GPIO_InitTypeDef structure.
ARM GAS  /tmp/cchbHOvP.s 			page 3


  70:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c ****         (++) In alternate mode is selection, the alternate function connected to the IO
  71:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c ****              is configured through "Alternate" member from GPIO_InitTypeDef structure.
  72:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c ****         (++) Analog mode is required when a pin is to be used as ADC channel
  73:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c ****              or DAC output.
  74:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c ****         (++) In case of external interrupt/event selection the "Mode" member from
  75:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c ****              GPIO_InitTypeDef structure select the type (interrupt or event) and
  76:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c ****              the corresponding trigger event (rising or falling or both).
  77:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c **** 
  78:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c ****     (#) In case of external interrupt/event mode selection, configure NVIC IRQ priority
  79:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c ****         mapped to the EXTI line using HAL_NVIC_SetPriority() and enable it using
  80:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c ****         HAL_NVIC_EnableIRQ().
  81:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c **** 
  82:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c ****     (#) To get the level of a pin configured in input mode use HAL_GPIO_ReadPin().
  83:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c **** 
  84:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c ****     (#) To set/reset the level of a pin configured in output mode use
  85:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c ****         HAL_GPIO_WritePin()/HAL_GPIO_TogglePin().
  86:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c **** 
  87:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c ****     (#) To set the level of several pins and reset level of several other pins in
  88:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c ****         same cycle, use HAL_GPIO_WriteMultipleStatePin().
  89:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c **** 
  90:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c ****     (#) To lock pin configuration until next reset use HAL_GPIO_LockPin().
  91:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c **** 
  92:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c ****     (#) During and just after reset, the alternate functions are not
  93:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c ****         active and the GPIO pins are configured in analog mode (except JTAG
  94:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c ****         pins).
  95:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c **** 
  96:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c ****     (#) The LSE oscillator pins OSC32_IN and OSC32_OUT can be used as general purpose
  97:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c ****         (PC14 and PC15, respectively) when the LSE oscillator is off. The LSE has
  98:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c ****         priority over the GPIO function.
  99:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c **** 
 100:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c ****     (#) The HSE oscillator pins OSC_IN/OSC_OUT can be used as
 101:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c ****         general purpose PH0 and PH1, respectively, when the HSE oscillator is off.
 102:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c ****         The HSE has priority over the GPIO function.
 103:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c **** 
 104:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c ****   @endverbatim
 105:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_gpio.c ****   */
